              <hi rend="b">
                <hi rend="i">Dark Visions: Blake’s Night Thoughts</hi>
              </hi>
            </title>
          </head>
          <p>Saturday, 1 October 1994</p>
          <p>The Centre for British Studies, Department of English, University of Adelaide, Adelaide 5005,
Australia, tel. 08-303-5625</p>
          <p>John E. Grant, “Who’s Who in Night Thoughts,” together with Michael J. Tolley, “Dark
Visions of Morality,” and Peter Otto, “Night Thoughts in Blake’s <hi rend="i">Four Zoas</hi>,” Mark
Davies, “Milton, Young and Blake,” Jon Mee, “Politics and Society in <hi rend="i">Night
Thoughts</hi>,” will present a workshop on Blake’s illustrations to Young’s poem. The venue will be the
University of Adelaide and the sponsor is the Centre for British Studies.</p>
          <p>Contact Margaret Hood, Box 1372, Aldinga Beach, South Australia 5173.</p>
        </div2>
